HEADWORD: Cossack post
<hw>Cos"sack post</hw>. <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>An outpost consisting of
four men, forming one of a single line of posts substituted for the more
formal line of sentinels and line of pickets.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cossas</ent>⟦br⟧
